HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 917
By Darby
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Westview High
School football team, TSSAA Division I, Class
3A state champion.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Westview High School football team achieved an extraordinary level of
success during the 2025 season, winning the coveted Tennessee Secondary School Athletic
Association (TSSAA) Division I, Class 3A State Football Championship; and
WHEREAS, the Westview Chargers vanquished every opponent for an undefeated
season on their way to the BlueCross Bowl championship game on December 5, 2025, at Finley
Stadium in Chattanooga, where they beat Gatlinburg-Pittman High School in the title matchup;
and
WHEREAS, on their path to the championship game, the Chargers defeated Hamilton
68-0, Westmoreland 55-7, Melrose 44-6, Covington 40-34, and finally Gatlinburg-Pittman 62-21,
to secure the right to hoist the iconic gold football trophy; and
WHEREAS, the victory saw Westview High School claim its second football State
championship in school history and tie or break nine separate State title game records in the
process, including a 99-yard touchdown pass, the longest pass play in a State championship
game; and
WHEREAS, the 2025 Westview Chargers enjoyed the services of an outstanding
coaching staff led by Head Coach Matt McConnell, who instilled in these exceptional young men
a commitment to excellence in all that they do and encouraged maximum effort on the football
field; and
HJR0917
012902
- 1 -

WHEREAS, State championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication, and
the ability to work together as a team and excel with a cooperative spirit; the Chargers exhibited
each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
WHEREAS, the football players of Westview High School epitomize all that is good in
today's student athletes, as they have achieved the highest level of success on the field while
showing the highest degree of character both on and off the gridiron; they inspired their fellow
students and united the entire community during their triumphant run through the 2025 season;
and
WHEREAS, the dedication, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of young
men not only made possible a championship football season but also surely bode well for their
success in every future endeavor; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the football players of
Westview High School for serving as exemplars of the high quality of the youth of Tennessee;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the players, coaching staff, team support staff,
administrators, cheerleaders, and fans of the Westview High School football team on winning
the 2025 TSSAA Division I, Class 3A State Football Championship.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
